{
  "doc_id": "9021",
  "text": "The mutated RsXI-C1O library, produced by errorprone PCR (see above), was mixed with SacII and XhoI digested pRS316GAP, and directly introduced into the W600W strain using the gap repair cloning protocol [CITATION_1] . The resulting yeast transformants were cultured in SD medium for 2 days. The non-mutated DNA fragment (control), amplified by PCR using pRS436GAP-RsXIC1O as the template, was introduced into the W600W strain in the same way as described above.",
